CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1955, pg. 32, reads: "In Carver Tribute - L.B. Toomer, center, Registrar of the United States Treasury, paid tribute to George Washington Carver in Pittsburgh last Sunday at the eleventh annual memorial service in Trinity Cathedral downtown, in honor of Dr. Carver. Left to right: Miss Myra Johns, Mrs. Alma Illery, founder of the National Achievement Clubs, who succeeded eleven years ago in having Congress unanimously recognize the George Washington Carver observance; Mr. Toomer and the Very Rev. N.R.H. Moor, dean of Trinity Cathedral. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Myra Johns, Alma Illery, L. B.Toomer, and Rev. N. R. H. Moor, standing under pulpit in Trinity Cathedral for George Washington Carver Day memorial service
